\id JDG Matupi Chin Standard Bible (MCSB)
\h LAITLOEKKUNG
\toc1 LAITLOEKKUNG
\toc2 Laitloek
\toc3 Ltk
\mt1 LAITLOEKKUNG
\mt2 (The Book of Judges)
\is1 Laitloekkung Cabu Kawng
\im But after the death of the judge, the people once again fall away from the Lord, and the pattern repeats itself. Even though the people make the same mistakes over and over, the Lord repeatedly reaches out to the people and offers them a chance to renew their agreement with him.
\im Joshua kah a dueknah hnukah (\sc b.c. 1200\sc* tuluk) tah pilnam aka cului ham mawtkung khat khaw om pawh. Pathen kah pilnam loh taklohnah muep a tong. Israel ca laklo ah olcen-kama khaw om. Kanaan pilnam neh caemtloeknah om. Kholong kah bawknah loh Israel ca rhoek te YHWH taeng lamloh a hnukpoh sak. Pathen loh Israel ca bom hamla khoboei lailtoekkung rhoek te a coelh pah. Amih loh pilnam dumlai a thui tih lai a tloek pah. Caem la a thoh vaengah pilnam paca a hueh tih a coi uh. Hekah cabu dongah he a niing la om coeng, Pathen olkhueng a poe uh vaengah amih toel hamla Pathen loh rhalcak neh thunkha a tueih pah. Pilnam loh bomnah te tungaepnah ham a pang uh vaengah Pathen loh laitloekung a tueih pah tih thunkha te a thup pah. Laitloekkung a dueknah hnukah tah pilnam te \nd Boeipa\nd* taeng lamloh hnukpoh uh tih amah pawtlawt la om uh. Tholh te koep koep a khoep uh tih paipi koepkoep a saii. He kah cabu he Jerusalem a po phoeikah 700 \sc b.c.\sc* tluk ah a tael tih 587 \sc b.c\sc* tluk vaengah a thai koep picai coini a ti.
\iot Sawt Yoeinah
\io1 Israel loh Kanaan a loh te hnukpoh uh \ior 1. 1—3. 6\ior*
\io1 Israel hlangcoelh laitloekkung rhoek \ior 3. 7—16. 31\ior*
\io1 Israel kah puencaknah \ior 17. 1—21. 25\ior*
\c 1
\s1 Judah neh Kanaan Rhal Uh
\p 
